---
import DocLayout from '../../layouts/DocLayout.astro';
import PropsTable from '../../components/PropsTable.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../components/CodeBlock.astro';
import StorybookPreview from '../../components/StorybookPreview.astro';
import LiveAvatarDemo from '../../components/react/LiveAvatarDemo';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL || '/storyhouse-design-system/';
const currentPath = `${base}components/avatar`;
---

<DocLayout
  title="Avatar"
  status="stable"
  description="User avatar component with image support, name-based initials fallback, multiple sizes and shapes."
>
  <section>
    <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
    <p>
      The <code>Avatar</code> component renders user profile images with intelligent fallbacks. It gracefully
      degrades from image → name initials → default icon. Each avatar uses a deterministic color based on
      the user's name, making grouped avatars visually distinct without manual color assignment.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="live-demo">Live Demo</h2>
    <p>The Avatar component in action — sizes, initials with automatic colors, and shapes.</p>
    <div class="my-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm dark:border-gray-800 dark:bg-gray-900">
      <LiveAvatarDemo client:load />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="sizes">Sizes</h2>
    <p>Five sizes from extra-small (24px) to extra-large (72px).</p>

    <div class="my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm dark:border-gray-800 dark:bg-gray-900">
      <div class="relative inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full overflow-hidden" style="width:24px;height:24px;background:#3b82f6">
        <span class="text-xs font-medium text-white" style="font-size:0.75rem;line-height:1rem">JD</span>
      </div>
      <div class="relative inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full overflow-hidden" style="width:32px;height:32px;background:#22c55e">
        <span class="text-sm font-medium text-white">JD</span>
      </div>
      <div class="relative inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full overflow-hidden" style="width:40px;height:40px;background:#a855f7">
        <span class="text-base font-medium text-white">JD</span>
      </div>
      <div class="relative inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full overflow-hidden" style="width:56px;height:56px;background:#ec4899">
        <span class="text-lg font-medium text-white">JD</span>
      </div>
      <div class="relative inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full overflow-hidden" style="width:72px;height:72px;background:#eab308">
        <span class="text-xl font-medium text-white">JD</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <CodeBlock title="avatar-sizes.tsx" code={`import { Avatar } from '@storyhouse/components';

export function AvatarSizes() {
  return (
    <div className="flex items-center gap-3">
      <Avatar name="Jane Doe" size="xs" />
      <Avatar name="Jane Doe" size="sm" />
      <Avatar name="Jane Doe" size="md" />
      <Avatar name="Jane Doe" size="lg" />
      <Avatar name="Jane Doe" size="xl" />
    </div>
  );
}`} />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="image">Image Avatar</h2>
    <p>Provide a <code>src</code> prop to show a user photo. Falls back to initials on image error.</p>

    <CodeBlock title="avatar-image.tsx" code={`import { Avatar } from '@storyhouse/components';

export function AvatarImage() {
  return (
    <div className="flex items-center gap-3">
      <Avatar src="/path/to/photo.jpg" alt="Jane Doe" />
      <Avatar name="John Smith" />
    </div>
  );
}`} />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="initials">Initials Fallback</h2>
    <p>
      When no <code>src</code> is provided, the avatar extracts up to 2 initials from the <code>name</code> prop
      and assigns a deterministic background color based on the name hash. This means the same name always
      gets the same color.
    </p>

    <CodeBlock title="avatar-initials.tsx" code={`import { Avatar } from '@storyhouse/components';

export function AvatarInitials() {
  return (
    <div className="flex items-center gap-3">
      <Avatar name="Alice Doe" />
      <Avatar name="Bob King" />
      <Avatar name="Carol Lee" />
    </div>
  );
}`} />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="shape">Shape</h2>
    <p>Choose between <code>circle</code> (default) and <code>square</code> variants.</p>

    <CodeBlock title="avatar-shape.tsx" code={`import { Avatar } from '@storyhouse/components';

export function AvatarShape() {
  return (
    <div className="flex items-center gap-3">
      <Avatar name="Jane Doe" variant="circle" />
      <Avatar name="Jane Doe" variant="square" />
    </div>
  );
}`} />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="fallback-icon">Fallback Icon</h2>
    <p>When neither <code>src</code> nor <code>name</code> is provided, a default user icon is rendered. You can override it with <code>fallback</code>.</p>

    <CodeBlock title="avatar-fallback.tsx" code={`import { Avatar } from '@storyhouse/components';

export function AvatarFallback() {
  return (
    <div className="flex items-center gap-3">
      <Avatar alt="User avatar" />
      <Avatar fallback={<span>&#x1F916;</span>} />
    </div>
  );
}`} />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="edge-cases">Edge Cases &amp; Error States</h2>

    <h3>Image Load Failure and Recovery</h3>
    <p>
      When an image fails to load (broken URL, network error), the component falls back to showing
      initials (if <code>name</code> is provided) or the default user icon. The error state is tracked
      via internal <code>imgError</code> state. If the <code>src</code> prop changes after an error,
      the <code>imgError</code> state is automatically reset, allowing the new image to load. This
      means dynamic avatar changes (e.g., browsing through a user gallery) work seamlessly without
      requiring a <code>key</code> prop workaround.
    </p>

    <CodeBlock title="avatar-src-change.tsx" code={`import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { Avatar } from '@storyhouse/components';

export function AvatarSrcChange() {
  const [src, setSrc] = useState(
    'https://example.com/broken.jpg'
  );

  return (
    <div className="flex flex-col items-start gap-3">
      <Avatar src={src} name="Jane Doe" alt="Jane Doe" />
      <button onClick={() => setSrc('https://i.pravatar.cc/150?u=jane')}>
        Load Valid Image
      </button>
    </div>
  );
}`} />

    <h3>Single-Word Names</h3>
    <p>
      A single-word name like <code>"Alice"</code> produces a single initial (<code>"A"</code>).
      The component splits on spaces and takes the first letter of each word, up to two initials.
    </p>

    <h3>Names with Special Characters</h3>
    <p>
      Names containing special characters (hyphens, apostrophes, diacritics) work correctly for
      initial generation. For example, <code>"Jean-Claude"</code> produces <code>"JC"</code>.
      The color hash operates on the full string, including special characters.
    </p>

    <h3>Very Long Names</h3>
    <p>
      The component caps initials at two characters regardless of name length.
      <code>"Mary Elizabeth Catherine"</code> produces <code>"ME"</code> — only the first two
      initials are used.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="best-practices">Best Practices &amp; Usage Guidelines</h2>

    <h3>When to Provide Which Props</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Both src and name</strong> — Best for user lists. Shows the photo on load, falls
        back to initials if the image fails.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>name only</strong> — Good for team lists, comment authors, and user mentions
        where images aren't guaranteed.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>src only (with alt)</strong> — For decorative user photos or when you know images
        will load reliably.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>fallback only</strong> — For anonymous users, bots, system accounts, or
        placeholder states.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Avatar Groups</h3>
    <p>
      For overlapping avatar groups (collaborators, multi-select), use negative margin on adjacent
      avatars:
    </p>

    <CodeBlock title="avatar-group.tsx" code={`import { Avatar } from '@storyhouse/components';

export function AvatarGroup() {
  return (
    <div className="flex">
      <Avatar name="Alice" className="-mr-2 ring-2 ring-white" />
      <Avatar name="Bob" className="-mr-2 ring-2 ring-white" />
      <Avatar name="Carol" className="-mr-2 ring-2 ring-white" />
      <Avatar name="Dave" className="ring-2 ring-white" />
    </div>
  );
}`} />

    <h3>Accessibility</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Image avatars use native <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> with <code>alt</code> attribute</li>
      <li>Always provide <code>alt</code> for image avatars — use the user's name</li>
      <li>Always provide <code>name</code> — it generates <code>title</code> and <code>aria-label</code></li>
      <li>Fallback and initials avatars use <code>role="img"</code> with <code>aria-label</code></li>
      <li>Deterministic colors help users recognize their own avatar across sessions</li>
      <li>All color backgrounds maintain WCAG AA contrast with white text</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="implementation">Implementation Details</h2>

    <h3>Fallback Chain</h3>
    <p>
      The component implements a three-tier fallback system with error recovery:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Image</strong> — Rendered when <code>src</code> is provided and <code>imgError</code> is false</li>
      <li><strong>Initials</strong> — Rendered when no valid image is present but <code>name</code> is provided</li>
      <li><strong>Default Icon</strong> — Rendered when neither <code>src</code> nor <code>name</code> is available</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
      The <code>imgError</code> state is set to <code>true</code> by the <code>onError</code> handler
      on the <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> element. This state is automatically reset when the
      <code>src</code> prop changes via a <code>useEffect</code> hook, allowing the component to
      reattempt loading a new image URL.
    </p>

    <h3>Deterministic Name Color</h3>
    <p>
      The <code>getNameColor</code> function uses a simple hash algorithm over the name string to
      pick from 8 background colors (blue, green, purple, pink, yellow, red, indigo, teal). The same
      name always produces the same color because the hash is purely deterministic — no random
      component. This is important for consistent UX across page loads and sessions.
    </p>

    <h3>Size Dimensions</h3>
    <p>
      Size is controlled via inline <code>width</code> and <code>height</code> styles using the
      <code>sizeDimensions</code> lookup table. The table also defines <code>text</code> classes and
      <code>iconSize</code> for the fallback SVG icon, ensuring text and icons scale proportionally
      with the avatar container.
    </p>

    <h3>Dark Mode</h3>
    <p>
      Avatar uses deterministic colors that work well on both light and dark backgrounds. The
      colors are bright enough to contrast with both white and dark gray backgrounds. All text
      on color backgrounds is white for consistent readability.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="props">Props</h2>
    <PropsTable
      rows={[
        { name: 'src', type: 'string', default: '-', description: 'Image URL. Falls back to initials on error.' },
        { name: 'alt', type: 'string', default: '""', description: 'Alt text for the image. Used as aria-label on fallback.' },
        { name: 'name', type: 'string', default: '-', description: 'User name for initials extraction and color generation.' },
        { name: 'size', type: '"xs" | "sm" | "md" | "lg" | "xl"', default: '"md"', description: 'Avatar dimensions from 24px to 72px.' },
        { name: 'variant', type: '"circle" | "square"', default: '"circle"', description: 'Shape variant.' },
        { name: 'fallback', type: 'React.ReactNode', default: '-', description: 'Custom fallback icon when no image or name is provided.' },
        { name: 'className', type: 'string', default: '-', description: 'Additional CSS classes.' },
      ]}
    />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="accessibility">Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Image avatars use native <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> with <code>alt</code> attribute</li>
      <li>Fallback avatars use <code>role="img"</code> and <code>aria-label</code> with the alt or name text</li>
      <li>Initials avatars have a <code>title</code> attribute for hover tooltip</li>
      <li>Deterministic colors mean users always recognize their avatar</li>
      <li>Sufficient contrast ratio on all deterministic color backgrounds with white text</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="storybook-preview">Interactive Preview</h2>
    <p>Explore all Avatar variants and props interactively in Storybook:</p>
    <StorybookPreview id="components-avatar--withimage" title="Avatar — Storybook" height="500" />
  </section>
</DocLayout>
